# clang-format Code Formatting

## Requirement

All C source and header files SHALL be formatted using clang-format.

A `.clang-format` configuration file SHALL be present in the project root or appropriate directory.

The `.clang-format` file SHALL be committed to version control.

All C files SHALL conform to the formatting style defined in `.clang-format`.

The Makefile `format` target SHALL use clang-format to check or apply formatting.

Formatting SHALL be checked in pre-commit hooks or CI/CD pipelines.

Code formatting SHALL be consistent across all C files in the project.

